      <acttitle>Local Government Act</acttitle>
      <title>Interim Regulations</title>
      <content>
        <section toc="false">
          <marginalnote>References to <actname>Local Government Act</actname></marginalnote>
          <sectionnumber>1</sectionnumber>
          <sectiontext>In this regulation, <term>Act</term> means the <actname>Local Government Act</actname>.</sectiontext>
        </section>
        <section>
          <marginalnote>Official community plans in process</marginalnote>
          <sectionnumber>2</sectionnumber>
          <sectiontext>Section 879 of the Act, as enacted by section 135 of the <actname>Local Government Statutes Amendment Act, 2000</actname>, does not apply to an official community plan that was subject to a public hearing in accordance with the Act as it read before that section came into force.</sectiontext>
        </section>
        <provisionsnote>[Provisions of the <actname>Local Government Act</actname>, R.S.B.C. 1996, c. 323, relevant to the enactment of this regulation: section 6.7]</provisionsnote>
      </content>
